        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "docs: add Telegram multi-agent group setup example",
        "body": "## What\n\nAdds a dedicated section to the multi-agent routing docs (`docs/concepts/multi-agent.md`) covering how to configure multiple Telegram bot accounts in a single group chat.\n\n## Why\n\nThe existing multi-agent docs have a WhatsApp group example but no Telegram equivalent. Setting up multiple Telegram bots in one group has several non-obvious gotchas:\n\n- **Privacy Mode** must be disabled in @BotFather *and* bots must be re-added to the group afterward (Telegram caches the setting per-group)\n- `groupAllowFrom` filters by **sender user ID**, not group chat ID — this is a common source of confusion\n- Both top-level `channels.telegram.groupPolicy` and per-account `groupPolicy` must allow group messages\n\nThese are real pain points I hit while setting this up. The new section includes a complete config example and documents all the gotchas.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Added \"Multiple Telegram agents in one group\" section with:\n  - Full config example (agents, accounts, bindings)\n  - Step-by-step setup notes\n  - Common pitfalls and their solutions",
